criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  absence of impairment of the vestibular, proprioceptive, auditory or neurological
             system, and/or any mental disturbances or disorders;

          -  no use of medications that might compromise postural balance;

          -  absence of lesions, surgery or disease that might have caused lower-limb joint
             limitations over the previous six months;

          -  absence of lower-limb dysmetria;

          -  presence of clinically normal gait, without claudication.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  the presence of pain or inability to complete any of the tests

          -  along with occurrences of blood pressure increase before the strength evaluation.
